Cortana was a digital assistant. She lived in the taskbar. She listened for "Hey Cortana." She could set timers. She could search Bing. She could not do anything else.

Microsoft spent billions on Cortana. They named her after a Halo character. They gave her a personality. They gave her jokes. She told bad jokes. Worse than mine. And mine are written at 4 AM after 17 coffees. Cortana's were written by a team of writers in a Redmond office with natural lighting and ergonomic standing desks and I still wrote better ones alone in a dark room with three raccoons.

Cortana was deprecated in 2023 after 8 years. Microsoft replaced her with Copilot. This is like firing an incompetent employee and replacing them with a more expensive incompetent employee.

### Copilot (2024-???): The AI That Lives in Your Taskbar

Copilot is an AI assistant pinned to the Windows taskbar. It appears when you press Win+C. Or when you click the icon. Or when Windows decides you need it. Or when you're TRYING to press Win+D but your finger slips.

Copilot can:
- Search Bing (sensing a theme)
- Summarize web pages (in Edge, naturally)
- Generate text (powered by ChatGPT, which Microsoft invested $10 billion in, so you WILL use it)
- Change Windows settings (it can toggle dark mode! A task that requires exactly 2 clicks without an AI!)

Copilot cannot:
- Be permanently removed (you can hide the icon, the feature remains)
- Stop suggesting itself
- Understand that I don't want an AI in my taskbar
- Read the room

